Copyright 2026 Jack Hosemans

This product includes software developed with reference to:

- treideme/brother_pt (https://github.com/treideme/brother_pt), Apache-2.0.
  Used as the hardware-verified reference implementation of the Brother
  raster protocol; this component's command streams are validated byte-exact
  against it (see host/gen_oracle.py).

- packbits 0.6 by Mikhail Korobov (https://github.com/kmike/packbits), MIT.
  ptouch_packbits_encode() in src/ptouch_raster.c is a C port of that
  package's encoder state machine (including its run-boundary quirks), so
  generated raster streams match the brother_pt reference byte-for-byte.
  The complete required MIT notice is included in THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md.

Protocol facts are from the Brother "Raster Command Reference"
(PT-E550W / P750W / P710BT).

PT-1950 setup semantics were independently determined from Brother's official
PT-1950/1960 Windows driver 6.02.00.00 (2010-03-02): package
pd1950w550axpus.exe SHA-256
76bb2706e0412f47989ab223de34da60c23f84424b81f17e1377b4e40c60f9e9 and
pt19v.dll SHA-256
ee594b196e200a2bdc35e867963b557a09afa6cf46d8e9b85cd9deb0e12c2537.
Only protocol interoperability facts are expressed here; no proprietary
driver code or data is copied or linked.

The model catalog also independently expresses USB identities and semantic
interoperability facts checked against ptouch-print commit
f7cce686099df3034fc41e427ab14358277234fe (GPL-3.0-or-later). No ptouch-print
source, flag layout, comments, or data structure is copied into or linked with
this Apache-2.0 component.
